  "text": "Note that we reported in an earlier study that NMDA stimulation results in a decrease of Grin2b in neurons [CITATION_1] . Our data presented here indicate that Grin2b expression is upregulated after the activation of the NMDA receptor. This difference is likely due to the degree of activation of the NMDA receptor. In our previous study, 100 μM NMDA was used to stimulate neurons, while 10 μM NMDA was applied in the current study.",
